ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‹Å“Adla BadliÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢ is comic-drama starring veteran duo Sachin Pilgaonkar and Ashok Saraf. Ram (Viju Khote) and Shaam (Anand Abhyankar) are business partners. They have an unusual habit of betting with each other for insignificant reasons. They both have different opinions about human tendency. According to Ram, human tends to behave as per the situation around him, whereas Shaam believes that no matter what the situation is, it cannot change the core of humanÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã¢â€žÂ¢s nature. The duo challenges each other and decides to have real-life experience of human tendency. For a mere bet of ten rupees, this rich duo creates such situations that their honest and successful employee Vaibhav (Sachin Pilgaonkar) is forced to see the world of poverty, whereas, a laidback beggar named Chandu (Ashok Saraf) lives the life of a rich businessman. At this point, their lives take drastic turns. Vaibhav realizes the true value of humanity, while Chandu comes across the lack of humanity in high society. Chandu and Vaibhav learn that Ram and Shaam are spoiling their lives for a mere bet. They decide to even the scores by teaching Ram and Shaam a lesson.

